OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Peter J. Fluor  Chief Executive Officer and Chairman, Texas Crude Energy, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships69--
Background

		Mr. Peter J. Fluor has been the Chief Executive Officer of Texas Crude Energy, Inc. since January 2001. Mr. Fluor served as the Chief Executive Officer and President at Texas Crude Energy, Inc. since 1980. He joined Texas Crude Energy, Inc. in 1972 and in positions with increasing responsibilities, including President from 1980 to 1990 and Chief Executive Officer from 1990 to 2001. He has been the Chairman at Texas Crude Energy, Inc. since January 2001. He served as ... the Non Executive Chairman of Fluor Corporation, from January 1998 to July 1998. Mr. Fluor has been a Director of Cooper Cameron Corp., since February 17, 2005; He has been a Director at Fluor Corp.(also know as Cibolo Creek Infrastructure JV) since 1984 and has been its Lead Independent Director since February 2003. He has been an Independent Director at Anadarko Petroleum Corporation since August 2007. He serves as a Director of The Welch Foundation. He served as a Director of Cameron International Corporation since February 17, 2005 until April 1, 2016. He served as a Director of Devon Energy Corp., from 2003 to 2007. He served as a Director of Devon OEI Operating, Inc. from 1980 to 2003. He serves as a Member of the Advisory Board of J.P. Morgan Chase Houston, Houston, Texas. He is a Member of the All American Wildcatters, the American Petroleum Institute and The Counsel of Overseers of the Jesse H. Jones Graduate School of Management at Rice University.Read Full Background




