					  Fluor Corporation Appoints Peter J. Fluor as Lead Independent Director					







      Category:          

Archive, Business Groups (Corporate), Company (Fluor), Regions (North America) 



    Thursday, February 13, 2003 8:08 am EST  



      Dateline:          




                    ALISO VIEJO, Calif.        






EmailPDFPrintRSS 



      Public Company Information:          




NYSE:FLR 







      Fluor Corporation's (NYSE: FLR) board of directors today announced that 
      Peter J. Fluor has been elected as its lead independent director. All of 
      the company's directors, excluding Chairman and Chief Executive Officer 
      Alan Boeckmann, are independent.
    

      In this newly created role, Mr. Fluor's responsibilities include 
      presiding over all executive sessions of the board's independent 
      directors and consulting with Boeckmann regarding quarterly board 
      meeting agendas, schedules and information flow. He also will provide 
      guidance on director orientation for new board members. His initial term 
      is three years.
    

      "This new position will help improve free and open communication both 
      among our independent directors and between the independent directors 
      and our management team. We want to do everything we can to utilize the 
      breadth of talent and experience our board members possess and to foster 
      their active participation in the affairs of the company," Boeckmann 
      said. "Peter is an excellent choice for this position. His many years of 
      experience as a global business leader provide him an understanding of 
      issues that could impact Fluor. That experience -- combined with his 
      knowledge of Fluor's operations, his long-standing relations with our 
      board's directors, and his skills as a counselor and advisor -- well 
      equip him for this role."
    

      Mr. Fluor joined Fluor's board of directors in 1984 and currently chairs 
      its audit committee. He also is a member of its executive, governance, 
      and organization and compensation committees, and served as the 
      company's non-executive chairman during fiscal 1998.
    

      Mr. Fluor is chairman and chief executive officer of Texas Crude Energy, 
      Inc., a private, independent oil and gas exploration company based in 
      Houston, Texas, with operations in the United States, Canada, China and 
      Australia.
    

      Active in a variety of professional and civic organizations, Mr. Fluor 
      serves on the boards of J.P. Morgan Chase Houston and Ocean Energy, Inc. 
      He also is a member of the All-American Wildcatters, the American 
      Petroleum Institute and the Council of Overseers of the Jesse H. Jones 
      Graduate School of Administration at Rice University.
    

      Mr. Fluor earned a bachelor's degree in finance and a master's degree in 
      business administration from the University of Southern California.
    

      Fluor Corporation (NYSE: FLR) provides services on a global basis in the 
      fields of engineering, procurement, construction, operations, 
      maintenance and project management. Headquartered in Aliso Viejo, 
      Calif., Fluor is a Fortune 500 company with revenues of $10 billion in 
      fiscal year 2002. For more information, visit www.fluor.com.
    

      For further information, please contact: Media Relations, Jerry 
      Holloway, +1-949-349-7411, or Lori Serrato, +1-949-349-7420, or Investor 
      Relations, Lila Churney, +1-949-349-3909, or fax, +1-949-349-5375, all 
      of Fluor Corporation.
    


 








